  • Classes in model used by model 
    Class and Description
    Amount
    An abstract class to build the abstraction layers for CountThreeMonthSupply, ThreeMonthSupply, CountUnitSize, and UnitSize
    Barcode
    Class to represent the Barcode for an Item
    CountAmount
    Abstract class to further define CountThreeMonthSupply and CountUnitSize where the unit type will only be "count"
    CountThreeMonthSupply
    A class to represent a count three month supply, where unit type is always "count"
    Inventory
    Singleton class to manage the entire Inventory system
    IPersistence
    Interface which defines methods for persisting data
    Item
    Class to represent an individual Item in the Inventory Tracker
    NonCountAmount
    Abstract Class to further define Non Count Three Month Supply and UnitSize
    Product
    A class to represent a product
    ProductContainer
    A class to represent a product container
    ProductDescription
    Class to represent a Product description
    ProductGroup
    A class to represent a ProductGroup
    StorageUnit
    A class representing a Storage Unit
    ThreeMonthSupply
    Class to represent a three month supply with unit types other than "count"
    UnitSize
    Class to represent a unit size where the unit type is not "count"
    UnitType
    A defined set of units for defining unit size and three month supply in the Inventory Tracker.
    UpdateType
    Describes the possible actions that can occur to an object in the system.
